Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
redo(25.10)                                                        redo(25.10)

Name
       redo  -  Returns the design to the state it was in immediately prior to
       issuing the undo command

Syntax
       redo [-help]

       Returns the design to the state it was in immediately prior to  issuing
       the undo command. It can be used only to reinstate power planning, bump
       placement, and selected floorplanning and wire edit functions that were
       removed with the undo command.

       You  can use this command after you use the undo command for any of the
       following text commands:

              * Selected bump placement commands:

                * create_bump

                * deleteBumps

              * Selected floorplanning commands:

                * alignObject

                * flipOrRotateObject

                * setObjFPlanBox

                * setObjFPlanBoxList

                * setObjFPlanPolygon

                * snapFPlan

                * snapFPlanIO

                * spaceObject

              * Selected power planning commands:

                * addRing

                * addStripe

                * editPowerVia

                * sroute

              *

                All wire editor commands:

                *

                  editAddFillet

                * editAddPoly

                *

                  editAddRoute

                *

                  editAddTrimMetal

              *

                * editAddVia

                * editChangeLayer

                * editChangeNet

                * editChangeRule

                * editChangeStatus

                * editChangeVia

                * editCommitPoly

                * editCommitRoute

                * editCutWire

                * editDelete

                * editDeleteFillet

                * editDeselect

                * editDuplicate

                * editFixWideWires

                * editMerge

                * editMove

                * editResize

                * editRotate

                * editSelect

                * editSplit

                * editTrim

                * prepareForEcoRoute

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the redo command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man redo

Related Information
              * undo

              * Edit Menu chapter in the Menu Reference

